(\sin x+1)^2 - (\sin x-1)^2
(\sin x+1)(\sin x+1)
(\sin x-1)(\sin x-1)
a=\sin x+1
b=\sin x -1
\begin{align} (\sin x + 1)^2 - (\sin x - 1)^2 &= (\sin^2 x + 2\sin x + 1) - (\sin^2 x - 2\sin x + 1) & \textrm{(multiply out the brackets)} \\ &= \sin^2 x + 2\sin x + 1 - \sin^2 x + 2\sin x - 1 & \textrm{(take the negative of the second bracket)} \\ & = 2\sin x + 2\sin x & \textrm{(the }\sin^2x\textrm{ and 1 terms cancel)} \\ & = 4\sin x & \textrm{(collect everything together)} \end{align} 
